bug.short_desc: background bitmap image disappeared when I copy slide and paste in same odp and different odp file
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem:
After copying slide and pasting it in same or other odp file, all slides using same background turned skyblue color background.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
Fedora 24, libreoffice-impress.x86_64 1:5.1.4.2-4.fc24, libreoffice-core.x86_64 1:5.1.4.2-4.fc24
How reproducible:
copy and paste slide, turn background to skyblue color, but creating new slide is no problem.
Steps to Reproduce: 1. run impress and open any odp/ppt file. 2. copy slide and paste it anywhere including other odp/pdf file. 3. all slides using same background bitmap image change to skyblue color background.
Actual results:
lose slide template property(background bitmap)
Expected results:
keep slide template property(background bitmap)
Additional info:
Created attachment 1176680 no problem with creating new slide
Created attachment 1176681 problem occurred after copy and paste.

This appears to be a regression from...
